10234646/https://people.rit.edu/wlrgsh/HumeTreatise.pdf\n| archive-date = 2019-08-10\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| last1 = Kant\n| first1 = Immanuel\n| title = Critique of Pure Reason\n| date=1787\n| publisher = Cambridge University Press\n| edition=I998\n| url = http://strangebeautiful.com/other-texts/kant-first-critique-cambridge.pdf\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191209231819/http://strangebeautiful.com/other-texts/kant-first-critique-cambridge.pdf\n| archive-date = 2019-12-09\n}}\n* {{cite journal | ref = harv\n| first = David H.\n| last = Kaye\n| title = On 'Falsification' and 'Falsifiability': The First Daubert Factor and the Philosophy of Science\n| date = 2005\n| ssrn = 767086\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| last1 = Keuth\n| first1 = Herbert\n| title = The Philosophy of Karl Popper\n| date = 2004\n| orig-year = 2000 (in German)\n| publisher = Cambridge University Press\n| publication-date=2005\n| isbn = 9780521548304\n| edition = 1st English\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| last=Kasavin\n| first= Ilya\n| first2 = Evgeny\n| last2=  Blinov\n| title= David Hume and Contemporary Philosophy\n| chapter=Hume and Contemporary Philosophy: Legacy and Prospects\n| editor= Ilya Kasavin\n| publisher= Cambridge Scholars\n| date=2012\n| pages=1\u20139\n| chapter-url=https://www.cambridgescholars.com/download/sample/58491\n| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160917095549/https://www.cambridgescholars.com/download/sample/58491\n| archive-date=2016-09-17\n}}\n* {{cite journal | ref = {{harvid|Krafka|2002}}\n| last1 = Krafka\n| first1 = Carol L.\n| last2 = Miletich\n| first2= D. Dean P. \n| last3 = Cecil\n| first3 = Joe S.\n| last4 = Dunn\n| first4 = Meghan A. \n| last5 = Johnson\n| first5 = Mary T. \n| title = Judge and attorney experiences, practices, and concerns regarding expert testimony in federal civil trials \n| journal = Psychology, Public Policy, and Law\n| date = September 2002\n| volume = 8\n| issue = 3\n| pages = 309\u2013332\n| doi = 10.1037/1076-8971.8.3.309\n| url = https://www.fjc.gov/content/judge-and-attorney-experiences-practices-and-concerns-regarding-expert-testimony-federal-0\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| last = Kuhn\n| first = Thomas S.\n| editor-first = Imre\n| editor-last = Lakatos\n| editor-first2 = Alan\n| editor-last2 = Musgrave\n| date = 1965\n| chapter = Logic of discovery or psychology of research?\n| title =  Criticism and the Growth of Knowledge. Proceedings of the International Colloquium in the Philosophy of Science\n| volume = 4\n| publisher = Cambridge University Press\n| location =  London\n| doi = 10.1017/S0007087400011626\n| orig-year = Reprinted {{harvnb|Kuhn|1974}}\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| last = Kuhn\n| first = Thomas S.\n| date = 1974\n| chapter = Logic of discovery or psychology of research?\n| title = The Philosophy of Karl Popper\n| volume = II\n| editor-first = Paul Arthur\n| editor-last = Schilpp\n| publisher = Open Court\n| location = Illinois\n| isbn = 0875481426\n| orig-year = First published {{harvnb|Kuhn|1965}}\n}}\n* {{Cite book | ref = harv\n| last = Kuhn\n| first = Thomas S.\n| title = The Structure of Scientific Revolutions\n| location = Illinois\n| orig-year = First published 1962\n| publisher = University of Chicago Press \n| edition = 3rd \n| date = 1996  \n| title-link = The Structure of Scientific Revolutions\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| first = Imre\n| last = Lakatos\n| date = 1978\n| title = The Methodology of Scientific Research Programmes: Volume 1: Philosophical Papers\n| editor1-first = John\n| editor1-last = Worrall\n| editor2-first = Gregory\n| editor2-last = Curry\n| publisher = Cambridge University Press\n| location = Cambridge\n| edition = 1980\n| isbn = 0-521-28031-1\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| last = Lange\n| first = Marc\n| date = 2008\n| series = Handbook of the History of Logic\n| title = Inductive Logic\n| volume = 10\n| chapter =  Hume and the Problem of Induction\n| veditors = Gabbay D, Hartmann S, Woods J\n| publisher = Elsevier BV\n| pages = 43\u201391\n| chapter-url=http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.504.2727&rep=rep1&type=pdf\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20181018184412/http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.504.2727&rep=rep1&type=pdf\n| archive-date = 2018-10-18\n}}\n* {{Wikicite | ref = {{harvid|Life On Perth|2007}}\n| reference = {{cite web\n | title = Life On Perth\n | date=2007\n | url = http://www.lifeonperth.com/origin.htm\n | website = LifeonPerth.com\n | accessdate = 2018-04-17\n | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180417022857/http://www.lifeonperth.com/origin.htm\n | archive-date=2018-04-17\n }}\n}}\n* {{Cite web | ref = harv\n| url = https://www.iep.utm.edu/sci-ideo/\n| title = Science and Ideology\n| last = Martin\n| first = Eric\n| date = 2017-19f\n| year = 2017\n| website = Internet Encyclopedia of Philosophy\n| url-status=live\n| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191104075438/https://www.iep.utm.edu/sci-ideo/\n| archive-date=2019-11-04\n| access-date=4 November 2019\n}}\n* [[Nicholas Maxwell|Maxwell, Nicholas]] (2017) [http://www.ucl.ac.uk/ucl-press/browse-books/karl-popper-science-and-enlightenment Karl Popper, Science and Enlightenment], UCL Press, London. Free online.\n* Maxwell, Nicholas (2017) [http://www.paragonhouse.com/xcart/Understanding-Scientific-Progress-Aim-Oriented-Empiricism.html Understanding Scientific Progress: Aim-Oriented Empiricism], Paragon House, St. Paul.\n* {{cite journal | ref = harv\n| last1 = McGinn\n| first1 = Colin\n| title = Looking for a Black Swan\n| journal = The New York Review of Books\n| date = 2002\n| issue = November 21, 2002\n| pages = 46\u201350\n}}\n* {{Wikicite | ref = {{harvid|McLean v. Arkansas|1982}}\n| reference={{cite court\n | litigants = McLean v. Arkansas Board of Education\n | court = Eastern District of Arkansas\n | url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170716024320/http://law.justia.com/cases/federal/district-courts/FSupp/529/1255/2354824/%7Caccessdate%3D16 Jul 2017\n | date = January 5, 1982\n }}\n}}\n* {{Cite book | ref = harv\n| last = Miller\n| first = David\n| title = Critical Rationalism : A Restatement and Defence\n| date = 1994\n| publisher = Open Court\n| title-link = Critical Rationalism\n}}\n* {{Cite journal | ref = harv\n| last = Miller\n| first = David\n| title = Sokal and Bricmont: Back to the Frying Pan|journal=Pli\n| volume = 9\n| year = 2000\n| pages = 156\u201373\n| url = http://www2.warwick.ac.uk/fac/soc/philosophy/staff/miller/miller_pli_9.pdf\n| url-status = dead\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070928003401/http://www2.warwick.ac.uk/fac/soc/philosophy/staff/miller/miller_pli_9.pdf\n| archive-date = 2007-09-28\n| df =\n}}\n* {{Cite journal| ref = harv\n| last = Miller\n| first = David\n| title = Out of Error\n| year = 2006\n| publisher=Ashgate\n}}\n* {{cite journal | ref = harv\n| last1 = Miller\n| first1 = David\n| title = Some Hard Questions for Critical Rationalism\n| journal = Discusiones Filos\u00f3ficas \n| date = 2014\n| orig-year = [http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.482.6469&rep=rep1&type=pdf Original version in 2011]\n| volume = 15 \n| issue = 24\n| pages = 15\u201340 \n| url = http://www.scielo.org.co/scielo.php?script=sci_arttext&pid=S0124-61272014000100002&lng=en&tlng=en\n| issn = 0124-6127\n}}\n* {{Cite book | ref = harv\n| last = Mises\n| first = Ludwig von\n| year = 1998\n| title = Human Action: A Treatise on Economics\n| chapter = Purposeful Action and Animal Reaction\n| chapter-url = https://cdn.mises.org/Human%20Action.pdf\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200109033531/https://cdn.mises.org/Human%20Action.pdf\n| archive-date = 2020-01-09\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| last1 = Pennock\n| first1 = Robert T.\n| title= Tower of Babel: The Evidence Against the New Creationism\n| date = 2000\n| series = A Bradford Book\n| publisher = MIT Press\n| isbn = 978-0262661652\n| edition = 1st\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| last = Popper\n| first = Karl\n| title = The Logic of Scientific Discovery\n| publisher = Routledge \n| edition = 2002 pbk; 2005 ebook\n| date = 1959\n| url = https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Logic_of_Scientific_Discovery\n| archive-url = https://archive.org/details/PopperLogicScientificDiscovery/page/n25/mode/2up\n| archive-date = 2013-11-18\n| isbn = 978-0-415-27844-7\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| last = Popper\n| first = Karl\n| title = Conjectures and Refutations: The Growth of Scientific Knowledge\n| publisher = Routledge\n| location = London\n| date = 1963\n| isbn = 978-0-415-28594-0\n| edition=2002\n}}\n* {{cite web | ref = harv\n| last1 = Popper\n| first1 = Karl\n| title = Science as Falsification\n| year = 1963b\n| url = http://www.stephenjaygould.org/ctrl/popper_falsification.html\n| accessdate=2 May 2018\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180502201044/http://www.stephenjaygould.org/ctrl/popper_falsification.html\n| archive-date = 2018-05-02\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| last = Popper\n| first = Karl\n| title =Objective Knowledge: An Evolutionary Approach\n| url = https://archive.org/details/objectiveknowled00popp\n| url-access = registration\n| date=1972\n| publisher = Oxford University Press\n| location = New York\n| isbn = 978-0198750246|edition=2003\n}}\n* {{cite book| ref = harv\n| last = Popper\n| first = Karl\n| title = The Philosophy of Karl Popper\n| chapter = Replies to my critics\n| volume = II\n| editor-first = Paul Arthur\n| editor-last = Schilpp\n| publisher = Open Court\n| location = Illinois\n| pages = 961\u20131197\n| date = 1974\n| isbn = 0875481426\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| last1 = Popper\n| first1 = Karl\n| editor1-last = Bartley III\n| editor1-first = W.W.\n| title = Unended Quest: An Intellectual Autobiography\n| date = 1976\n| publisher = Routledge\n| location = London and New York\n| isbn = 0415285895\n| edition = 2002\n| url = https://books.google.com/?id=F_2WSLsDyvwC&pg=PA330#v=onepage&q&f=false\n}}\n* {{cite journal| ref = harv\n| last1 = Popper\n| first1 = Karl\n| journal = Dialectica\n| volume = 32\n| issue =3/4\n| pages =339\u2013355\n| title = Natural Selection and the Emergence of Mind\n| date = 1978\n| jstor = 42970324\n| doi=10.1111/j.1746-8361.1978.tb01321.x\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| last1 = Popper\n| first1 = Karl\n| editor1-last = Bartley III\n| editor1-first=W.W.\n| title = Quantum Theory and the Schism in Physics: From the Postscript to the Logic of Scientific Discovery\n| date = 1982\n| orig-year = originally written in 1962\n| publisher = Routledge\n| isbn =  0415091128\n| edition=2005\n}}\n* {{Cite interview | ref = harv\n| last = Popper\n| first = Karl\n| interviewer = S. Lannes and A. Boyer\n| title = Les chemins de la verite: L'Express va plus loin avec Karl Popper\n| work = L'Express\n| date = 26 February 1982\n| year = 1982b\n| pages = 82-88\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| last = Popper\n| first = Karl\n| title = Realism and the Aim of Science: From the Postscript to The Logic of Scientific Discovery\n| orig-year = originally written in 1962\n| date = 1983\n| publisher = Routledge\n| location = London and New York\n| isbn=0-415-08400-8\n| edition=1st\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| first = Karl\n| last = Popper\n| chapter = Zwei Bedeutungen von Falsifizierbarkeit [Two meanings of falsifiability]\n| language=german\n| editor1-first = H.\n| editor1-last = Seiffert\n| editor2-first = G.\n| editor2-last = Radnitzky \n| title = Handlexikon der Wissenschaftstheorie [Dictionary of epistemology]\n| publisher = Deutscher Taschenbuch Verlag \n| location = M\u00fcnchen \n| date = 1989\n| edition = 1992\n| isbn = 3-423-04586-8\n}}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv\n| first = Karl\n| last = Popper\n| year = 2009\n| orig-year = manuscript 1933, Published German 1979\n| editor-last = Eggers Hansen\n| editor-first = Troels\n| title = The Two Fundamental Problems of the Theory of Knowledge \n| publisher = Routledge \n|