shown within Hampshire\n| subdivision_name2       = [[South East England]]\n| subdivision_name3       = [[Hampshire]]\n| subdivision_name5       = [[Havant]]\n| established_date1       = 1 April 1974\n| governing_body          = Havant Borough Council\n| leader_party            = {{English district control|GSS=E07000090}}\n| leader_name             = [[Local Government Act 2000|Leader & Cabinet]]\n| leader_name1            = [[George Hollingbery]]<br/>[[Alan Mak (politician)|Alan Mak]]\n| area_total_km2          = 55.3\n| area_rank               = {{English district area rank|GSS=E07000090}} [[List of English districts by area|(of {{English district total}})]]\n| population_total        = {{English district population|GSS=E07000090}}\n| population_as_of        = {{English statistics year}}\n| population_rank         = {{English district rank|GSS=E07000090}} [[List of English districts by population|(of {{English district total}})]]\n| population_blank1       = 98.5% White\n| blank1_info             = 24UH (ONS)<br />E07000090 (GSS)\n| blank2_info             = {{gbmappingsmall|SU717062}} \n| website                 = {{URL|http://www.havant.gov.uk/}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Borough of Havant''' is a [[Non-metropolitan district|local government district]] and [[Borough status in the United Kingdom|borough]] in [[Hampshire]], [[England]].  Its council is based in [[Havant]].  Other places within the Borough include [[Bedhampton]], [[Cowplain]], [[Emsworth]], [[Hayling Island]], [[Purbrook]], [[Waterlooville]] and [[Widley]]. The Borough covers much of the semi-urban area in the south east of Hampshire, between the city of [[Portsmouth]] and the [[West Sussex]] border.\n\n==Havant Borough Council==\n{{see also|Havant Borough Council elections}}\nElections to the borough council are held in three out of every four years, with one third of the 38 seats on the council being elected at each election. The [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative party]] held a majority on the council  from 1978 until they lost a majority in 1990. No party had a majority until the [[2002 Havant Borough Council election|2002 election]] when the Conservatives regained overall control. Since then the Conservatives have had a majority and as of the [[2016 Havant Borough Council election|2016 election]] the council is composed of the following councillors:-<ref name=\"vote2014\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/politics/councils/E07000090|title=Havant|publisher=[[BBC News Online]]|accessdate=23 June 2014}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" | '''Party'''\n| valign=\"top\" | '''Councillors'''<br />\n|-\n{{party colour|Conservative Party (UK)}}\n| [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative Party]]\n| 31\n|-\n{{party colour|UKIP}}\n| [[UK Independence Party]]\n| 4\n|-\n{{party colour|Labour Party (UK)}}\n| [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]]\n| 2\n|-\n{{Party colour|Liberal Democrats (UK)}}\n| [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]]\n| 1\n|}\n\n===Wards===\nThe [[Wards and electoral divisions of the United Kingdom|wards]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.havant.gov.uk/havant-8160 |title=Havant Borough Council councillors |accessdate=2007-11-14 |work=www.havant.gov.uk |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071005090100/http://www.havant.gov.uk/havant-8160 |archivedate=2007-10-05 }}</ref> are:\n*[[Barncroft]]\n*[[Battins]]\n*[[Bedhampton]]\n*[[Bondfields]]\n*[[Cowplain]]\n*[[Emsworth]]\n*[[Hart Plain]]\n*[[Hayling East]]\n*[[Hayling West]]\n*[[Purbrook]]\n*[[St Faith's]]\n*Stakes\n*[[Leigh Park|Warren Park]]\n*[[Waterlooville]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of places of worship in the Borough of Havant]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.havant.gov.uk/ Havant Borough Council]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090725060736/http://www.havantboroughtreewardens.org.uk/ Havant Borough Tree Wardens ]\n{{Hampshire}}\n{{SE_England}}\n{{Havant}}\n{{Commons category|Borough of Havant|Havant}}\n{{coord|50.85088|-0.98284|type:landmark_region:GB_source:enwiki-osgb36(SU717062)|display=title}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Havant, Borough of}}\n[[Category:Borough of Havant| ]]\n[[Category:Non-metropolitan districts of Hampshire]]\n[[Category:Unparished areas in Hampshire]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See {{Infobox settlement}} for the full list of available fields -->\n<!-- Elements common to United Kingdom -->\n| timezone                = [[Greenwich Mean Time|GMT]]\n| utc_offset              = 0\n| timezone_DST            = [[British Summer Time|BST]]\n| utc_offset_DST          = +1\n\n<!-- Elements common to administrative division of this type (English two-tier district) -->\n| settlement_type         = [[Non-metropolitan district]]\n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Sovereign state]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[Countries of the United Kingdom|Constituent country]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[Regions of England|Region]]\n| subdivision_type3       = [[Non-metropolitan county]]\n| subdivision_type4       = Status\n| subdivision_type5       = Admin HQ\n| subdivision_name        = [[United Kingdom]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[England]]\n| subdivision_name4       = [[Non-metropolitan district]]\n| government_type         = Non-metropolitan district council\n| leader_title            = Leadership\n| leader_title1           = [[List of MPs elected in the 2015 United Kingdom general election|MPs]]\n| established_title1      = Incorporated\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_blank1_title = Ethnicity\n| blank1_name             = [[ONS coding system|ONS code]]\n| blank2_name             = [[Ordnance Survey National Grid|OS grid reference]]\n\n<!-- Elements unique to this article -->\n| official_name           = Borough of Havant \n| image_skyline           = \n| imagesize               = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_captio