il==\n{{see also|Havant Borough Council elections}}\nElections to the borough council are held in three out of every four years, with one third of the 38 seats on the council being elected at each election. The [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative party]] held a majority on the council  from 1978 until they lost a majority in 1990. No party had a majority until the [[2002 Havant Borough Council election|2002 election]] when the Conservatives regained overall control. Since then the Conservatives have had a majority and as of the [[2016 Havant Borough Council election|2016 election]] the council is composed of the following councillors:-<ref name=\"vote2014\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/politics/councils/E07000090|title=Havant|publisher=[[BBC News Online]]|accessdate=23 June 2014}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" | '''Party'''\n| valign=\"top\" | '''Councillors'''<br />\n|-\n{{party colour|Conservative Party (UK)}}\n| [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative Party]]\n| 31\n|-\n{{party colour|UKIP}}\n| [[UK Independence Party]]\n| 4\n|-\n{{party colour|Labour Party (UK)}}\n| [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]]\n| 2\n|-\n{{Party colour|Liberal Democrats (UK)}}\n| [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]]\n| 1\n|}\n\n===Wards===\nThe [[Wards and electoral divisions of the United Kingdom|wards]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.havant.gov.uk/havant-8160 |title=Havant Borough Council councillors |accessdate=2007-11-14 |work=www.havant.gov.uk |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071005090100/http://www.havant.gov.uk/havant-8160 |archivedate=2007-10-05 }}</ref> are:\n*[[Barncroft]]\n*[[Battins]]\n*[[Bedhampton]]\n*[[Bondfields]]\n*[[Cowplain]]\n*[[Emsworth]]\n*[[Hart Plain]]\n*[[Hayling East]]\n*[[Hayling West]]\n*[[Purbrook]]\n*[[St Faith's]]\n*Stakes\n*[[Leigh Park|Warren Park]]\n*[[Waterlooville]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of places of worship in the Borough of Havant]]